Q3: I just want to add a compliment to the dept. faculty: I've had a lot of health problems interfere with my schooling during my time at SU and teachers have had an incredible degree of patience and understanding while still holding me to the same academic standard as the other students in terms of the quality of my work. That's a really difficult balance to strike when working with a student with a developmental disability. I'm not given grades I don't deserve (I've done poorly when it was fair for me to do so), but I am given tons of opportunities to demonstrate my abilities despite those setbacks and I think that's a credit to this department's ability to work with students on an individual level.
